## Diagnosis

The two-axis grammar (color channel + weight channel) is structurally correct but the resting-state border weight is miscalibrated. A 2px border at rest is visually assertive — it reads as "engaged" even when idle, collapsing the weight axis so focus/hover can no longer communicate through thickness delta. The engaged state has no perceptible upgrade to offer.

**Anti-pattern: AP-072** — *Axis Collapse*: two design channels nominally exist but carry identical values, destroying the semantic distinction the grammar was meant to encode.

---

## Root Cause

The token or component CSS is setting `--input-border-width` (or equivalent) to `2px` unconditionally, rather than distinguishing:

| State | Color channel | Weight channel |
|---|---|---|
| Resting | muted/subtle | **1px** |
| Hover | slightly elevated | 1px |
| Focused | brand/accent | **2px** (paint-only ring) |
| Error | destructive | **2px** |
| Disabled | faint | 1px |

---

## Fix

### 1. Token layer — `src/tokens/components/input.css` (or `.ts`)

```css
/* src/tokens/components/input.css */

@layer elan.tokens {
  :root {
    /* ── Weight axis ─────────────────────────────────── */
    --input-border-width-resting:  1px;   /* hairline — was incorrectly 2px */
    --input-border-width-engaged:  2px;   /* focus / error upgrade          */

    /* ── Color axis ─────────────────────────────────── */
    --input-border-color-resting:  var(--color-border-default);
    --input-border-color-hover:    var(--color-border-strong);
    --input-border-color-focused:  var(--color-border-brand);
    --input-border-color-error:    var(--color-border-destructive);
    --input-border-color-disabled: var(--color-border-subtle);
  }
}
```

### 2. Component styles — `src/components/ui/Input/Input.css` (or the Tailwind variant)

```css
/* src/components/ui/Input/Input.css */

.input-base {
  /* Resting: hairline border, muted color */
  border-width: var(--input-border-width-resting);   /* 1px */
  border-color: var(--input-border-color-resting);
  border-style: solid;
  border-radius: var(--input-radius);

  /* Prevent layout shift on focus — reserve the extra pixel via outline,
     not border, so the engaged ring paints over rather than pushing content */
  outline-offset: -1px;   /* inset so it doesn't shift siblings */
  outline: var(--input-border-width-engaged) solid transparent;

  transition:
    border-color 120ms ease,
    outline-color 120ms ease;
}

/* ── Hover ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
.input-base:hover:not(:focus):not(:disabled) {
  border-color: var(--input-border-color-hover);
  /* weight stays at 1px — color channel carries the hover signal */
}

/* ── Focused: paint-only ring, zero layout shift ─────── */
.input-base:focus-visible {
  border-color: var(--input-border-color-focused);
  outline-color: var(--input-border-color-focused);
  /* border remains 1px; the 2px outline renders inset, no reflow */
}

/* ── Error ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
.input-base[aria-invalid="true"],
.input-base.is-error {
  border-color: var(--input-border-color-error);
  outline-color: var(--input-border-color-error);
}

/* ── Disabled ────────────────────────────────────────── */
.input-base:disabled {
  border-color: var(--input-border-color-disabled);
  /* weight stays 1px */
}
```

### 3. If you're using Tailwind utility classes in the component JSX — `src/components/ui/Input/Input.tsx`

```tsx
// src/components/ui/Input/Input.tsx

const inputVariants = cva(
  [
    // Weight axis: resting = hairline
    "border border-border-default",               // 1px resting — remove any `border-2`

    // Paint-only engaged ring (no layout shift)
    "outline outline-2 outline-transparent outline-offset-[-1px]",

    // Color + outline transitions
    "transition-[border-color,outline-color] duration-[120ms] ease-[ease]",

    // Hover: color channel only
    "hover:border-border-strong",

    // Focus: both channels activate
    "focus-visible:border-border-brand focus-visible:outline-border-brand",

    // Disabled
    "disabled:border-border-subtle disabled:cursor-not-allowed",
  ],
  {
    variants: {
      state: {
        default: "",
        error: [
          "border-border-destructive outline-border-destructive",
        ],
      },
    },
    defaultVariants: { state: "default" },
  }
);
```

> **Key mechanic**: `outline` is used for the engaged-weight upgrade, not `border-width`. `outline-offset: -1px` makes it inset so it renders inside the box — zero reflow, zero layout shift. The border stays 1px in all states; the outline provides the 2px visual weight at engagement.

---

## Principle

**Two-axis grammar requires distinct values on both axes at every state.** If the resting weight equals the engaged weight, the weight axis is mute — only color can signal state change, which fails users in low-color-discrimination conditions and reads as visually flat to everyone. Resting = 1px hairline preserves the full delta (1px → 2px) so focus reads as a genuine upgrade, not noise.
